@jorisvandenbossche in response to your API issue.

this is a bit of speculation, but I think that `to_datetime` was supposed to be the general convert me to datetimes, e.g. takes in a array/list/scalar and bunch of options to provide a very general parsing. While `Timestamp` is a pretty simple object with limited parsing.

That said, as long as it doesn't become a performance issue their is really no reason to not have `Timestamp` parse more generally.

